===2010 census===
As of the [[census]] of 2010, there were 1,351 people, 673 households, and 331 families in the city. The [[population density]] was {{convert|465.9|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|1}}. There were 863 housing units, with an average density of {{convert|297.6|/sqmi|/km2|1}}. The racial makeup of the city was 93.4% [[White (U.S. Census)|white]], 0.4% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 2.4% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.5% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.1% [[Race (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 0.6% from [[Race (U.S. Census)|other races]], and 2.5% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] and [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] residents of any race were 1.6% of the population.

There were 673 households, of which 21.5% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 37.1% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 9.4% had a female householder with no husband present, 2.7% had a male householder with no wife present, and 50.8% were non-families; 43.7% of all households were made up of individuals, and 18.6% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 1.94 persons, and the average family size was 2.67.

The median age in the city was 48.4 years; 18.1% of residents were under the age of 18; 5.1% were between the ages of 18 and 24; 23.2% were from 25 to 44; 30.8% were from 45 to 64; and 23% were 65 years of age or older. The gender makeup of the city was 45.9% male and 54.1% female.

===2000 census===
As of the [[census]] of 2000, there were 1,353 people, 645 households, and 341 families residing in the city. The population density was {{convert|506.7|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 722 housing units, with an average density of {{convert|270.4|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the city was 94.97% [[White (U.S. Census)|white]], 2.81% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.15% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.15% [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 0.07% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 1.85% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] and [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] residents of any race were 0.74% of the population. According to the census, 23.3% were of [[Norwegians|Norwegian]], 20.2% [[Germans|German]], 11.8% [[Swedish people|Swedish]], 7.0% [[Irish people|Irish]] and 6.1% [[English people|English]] ancestry.

[[File:Beaver House baitshop.JPG|thumb|200px|left|The giant walleye at Beaver House bait shop, a Grand Marais landmark]]
There were 645 households, of which 23.3% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 42.9% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 8.1% had a female householder with no husband present, and 47.1% were non-families; 42.0% of all households were made up of individuals, and 21.6% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.01 and the average family size was 2.73.

In the city 18.8% of the population were under the age of 18; 6.1% were from 18 to 24; 25.9% were from 25 to 44; 22.8% were from 45 to 64; and 26.3% were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 45. For every 100 females, there were 83.1 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 80.8 males.

The median income for a household in the city was $33,493, and the median income for a family was $46,563. Males had a median income of $31,500. The median income for females was $23,393. The [[per capita income]] for the city was $21,863. About 7.4% of families and 10.0% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 11.9% of those under age 18 and 12.0% of those age 65 or over.

